questions.scenario:
You are performing a Bug Hunter review on the following Spring Boot service snippet designed to process orders asynchronously:

java
@Service
public class OrderService {
    @Transactional
    public void placeOrder(Order order) {
        orderRepository.save(order);
        CompletableFuture.runAsync(() -> {
            paymentService.process(order);
            order.setStatus(Status.COMPLETED);
            orderRepository.save(order);
        });
    }
}

Users report that occasionally orders are saved with 'PENDING' status even when `paymentService` succeeds, and logs show `LazyInitializationException` or missing transaction context.
